Q. What is Kasumi Ninja?

A. Kasumi Ninja is the first announced fighting game being released for the
Atari Jaguar 64 Bit Multimedia System.  Its expected release date is
sometime early to mid November.  The game is being developed by Handmade
Software (based in the U.K.) for Atari Corp.  It will also be the first
4Meg (32 megabit) cart released for the Jaguar.
===============================================================
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
===============================================================

Q. What is "special" about KN?

A. KN represents the first Digitized fighting game to rival/exceed the
visuals, violence and gameplay of the Mortal Kombat series of arcade games
on the Atari Jaguar.  By using the Jaguar's advanced graphic and sound
capabilities, KN should be the first true "arcade" quality fighting game
available on the Jaguar.  One other note is about the violence in this
game.  This will undoubtedly be if not the bloodiest then one of the
bloodiest games in or out of the arcade.  To this end, Atari will be
voluntarily placing a warning on the outside and the inside of the game
package.  

NOTE:  There will be a "gore" setting whereby the player can easily turn on
and off the gore in the options menu.  Atari will have a "lock-out"
mechanism to censor the blood and fatalities for concerned parents.  This
mechanism will be a parent programmable password that can be entered and
changed to enable or disable the "gore" mode.
